# Professional Quotations & Administration Module

This plan outlines the implementation of a new module for the travel agency's admin panel to manage company settings, create professional quotes, and generate airport welcome signs for clients.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Changes**: We will create three new tables (`settings`, `quotations`, `quotation_items`). Ensure you have a backup of your current database before I run these SQL commands.

> [!NOTE]
> **Printing**: The "Print" features will be optimized for standard A4/Letter paper sizes using CSS `@media print`.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Layer

We need to store company identity and quotation data.

#### [NEW] `quotations_schema.sql` (Temporary scratch file)
```sql
-- Company Settings
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `settings` (
    `id` INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    `company_name` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    `company_address` TEXT,
    `company_phone` VARCHAR(100),
    `company_email` VARCHAR(255),
    `company_logo` VARCHAR(255),
    `default_tax_rate` DECIMAL(5,2) DEFAULT 18.00,
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

-- Quotations
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `quotations` (
    `id` INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    `quote_number` VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    `customer_name` VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    `customer_email` VARCHAR(255),
    `customer_phone` VARCHAR(50),
    `travel_date` DATE,
    `subtotal` DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    `tax_amount` DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    `total_price` DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    `notes` TEXT,
    `status` ENUM('draft', 'sent', 'confirmed', 'expired') DEFAULT 'draft',
    `created_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;

-- Quotation Line Items
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `quotation_items` (
    `id` INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    `quotation_id` INT NOT NULL,
    `item_type` ENUM('package', 'excursion', 'transfer', 'custom') NOT NULL,
    `item_id` INT DEFAULT NULL,
    `description` TEXT NOT NULL,
    `quantity` INT DEFAULT 1,
    `unit_price` DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    `total` DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (`quotation_id`) REFERENCES `quotations`(`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4 COLLATE=utf8mb4_general_ci;
```

